<br>
Two were family oriented, one seemed to be more raid oriented somewhat (all small/medium size guilds 20-40 people on-line prime times).<br>
<br>
Never saw an officer voted in in any of them, always appointed.<br>
<br>
Unique titles and duties in only one of the three.<br>
<br>
Decisions were made generally by the leaders.  Some topics were posted for comment on Guild Boards, but the decision rested in the leadership.  One of the things Dragonguard does is to have Class Loot Leaders who determined policies for Planes drops, etc., who was not necessarily an officer.  Raids can also be set up and run by any member.  While Guild policy would generally be enforced, raid leaders were the ultimate authority for their event and had the final say on any loot.<br>
<br>
Guild message boards were widely used in all three and were an excellent way of keeping in touch with people with varied play times all over Norrath.<br>
<br>
